    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1969-01-14T14:24:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1969-01-14T14:24:00-05:00" n="2"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d2">
                <head>2. Telegram 6001 From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to
                    the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Israel</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d2fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1967-69, POL 27 ARAB-ISR.
                        Unclassified. Repeated to Montreal, Ottawa, Beirut, London, and Rome.
                        Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_LFE1">Loy</persName> (<gloss target="#t_E1"
                            >E</gloss>/TT), cleared by <persName corresp="#p_DRP1">Roger P.
                            Davies</persName> (<gloss target="#t_NEA1">NEA</gloss>) and <persName
                            corresp="#p_SMH2">Styles</persName> (E/OA/AVP), and approved by
                            <persName corresp="#p_RD3">Rusk</persName>.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d2fn2">A message from Deputy Assistant
                        Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_LFE1">Loy</persName> to <gloss
                            target="#t_IATA1">IATA</gloss> Director-General <persName
                            corresp="#p_HK1">Knut Hammarskjold</persName> expressing U.S. concern
                        about recent hijackings. <persName corresp="#p_LFE1">Loy</persName>
                        condemned Israel for the attack on Khaldeh Airport in Lebanon and noted that
                        the U.S. had registered disapproval of the Athens hijacking of an El Al
                        aircraft.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1969-01-14T19:24:00+00:00">January 14, 1969, 1924Z</date>.</dateline>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>Subject:</head>
                    <item>IA <gloss target="#t_ICAO1">ICAO</gloss> Meeting on Beirut Airport
                        Raid</item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Israeli Emb Counselor Raviv called at Dept Jan 13 to discuss Jan 20
                        meeting of <gloss target="#t_ICAO1">ICAO</gloss> Council called consider
                        Lebanese complaint re Israeli Beirut raid. Read Israeli counter-complaint to
                            <gloss target="#t_ICAO1">ICAO</gloss> which dealt with attack on El Al
                        airplane in Athens and earlier hijacking in Algiers.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>In response to query, Deptoff stated <gloss target="#t_US1">US</gloss>
                        considered <gloss target="#t_ICAO1">ICAO</gloss> should not limit its
                        consideration to Beirut incident but should examine broader question of
                        threat presented to safe international air navigation by use of force and
                        violence. <gloss target="#t_US1">US</gloss> believed political aspects had
                        already been dealt with in Security Council and <gloss target="#t_ICAO1"
                            >ICAO</gloss> should concentrate on question of safeguarding
                        international civil aviation against all illegal interference. Stated USDEL
                        had replied in this vein to <gloss target="#t_ICAO1">ICAO</gloss> in
                        responding to notice of Jan 20 meeting.</item>
                </list>
                <pb facs="d2-02" n="2" xml:id="d2-02"/>
                <p> For Ottawa, Rome and London: Canadian, Italian and <gloss target="#t_UK1"
                        >UK</gloss> Embassies have inquired concerning <gloss target="#t_US1"
                        >US</gloss> attitude toward special <gloss target="#t_ICAO1">ICAO</gloss>
                    meeting. Canadians and British were given copy of <gloss target="#t_US1"
                        >US</gloss> reply to <gloss target="#t_ICAO1">ICAO</gloss> along above lines
                    and British have now informed us they will take similar position.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RD3">Rusk</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
